| TC ID       | Category   | Scenario / Objective                       | Steps                                                                        | Expected Result                                         | Risk   | Mitigation                                                   |
| ----------- | ---------- | ------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| TC-FUNC-01  | Functional | Submit dynamic form with all fields filled | Navigate to RPA Challenge → Start Challenge → Fill all fields → Click Submit | Form submits successfully; success message appears      | Medium | Use `get_by_label()` locators; auto-wait for elements        |
| TC-FUNC-02  | Functional | Validate success message after submission  | Same as TC-FUNC-01                                                           | Success message visible; no errors                      | Medium | Assert observable text instead of DOM structure              |
| TC-FUNC-03  | Functional | Validate form resets for next iteration    | Submit form → Observe new form                                               | Form loads fresh, fields cleared                        | Medium | Auto-waits; validate visible form                            |
| TC-NEG-01   | Negative   | Submit empty form                          | Start Challenge → Click Submit without entering values                       | Validation error appears; form not submitted            | High   | Use label/role-based locators; assert error message          |
| TC-NEG-02   | Negative   | Enter invalid email/phone                  | Fill all fields; enter invalid email/phone → Submit                          | Validation errors appear for invalid fields             | High   | Use `expect()` for validation; robust locators               |
| TC-NEG-03   | Negative   | Partial form submission                    | Fill some fields → Submit                                                    | Error message appears; incomplete submission blocked    | Medium | Assert visible error; fresh locator usage                    |
| TC-CHAOS-01 | Chaos      | Refresh page mid-form                      | Start Challenge → Fill some fields → Refresh                                 | Form resets safely; no crash                            | High   | Validate form reload; auto-wait for new elements             |
| TC-CHAOS-02 | Chaos      | Double-click Submit rapidly                | Fill all fields → Double-click Submit                                        | Only one submission accepted; success message displayed | High   | Assert correct submission; observe UI state                  |
| TC-CHAOS-03 | Chaos      | Partial submission repeated                | Fill partial fields → Submit multiple times                                  | System handles repeated attempts gracefully             | Medium | Observe UI messages; avoid stale locators                    |
| TC-STAB-01  | Stability  | Dynamic field reordering                   | Fill form multiple times → Observe field positions                           | Locators continue to work; test does not break          | Medium | Use `get_by_label()`, `get_by_role()`                        |
| TC-STAB-02  | Stability  | DOM re-render mid-fill                     | Fill first few fields → DOM refresh occurs                                   | Fields still interactable; no test failure              | Medium | Auto-wait, fresh locators; avoid storing element handles     |
| TC-PARA-01  | Parallel   | Multiple sessions concurrently             | Run 3 browser sessions in parallel → Submit forms independently              | All forms submitted successfully; no interference       | Medium | Isolated BrowserContext per session                          |
| TC-PARA-02  | Parallel   | Parallel form submissions                  | Multiple tests submit forms at the same time                                 | Each submission succeeds; no data leakage               | Medium | Parallel execution setup; verify observable success messages |
| TC-PARA-03  | Parallel   | Verify independent session data            | Fill form in multiple sessions → Observe stored data (if any)                | Each session independent; no shared data                | Medium | Use session isolation; assert observable UI feedback         |
| TC-NEG-04   | Negative   | Submit after partial refresh               | Fill some fields → Refresh → Submit                                          | Validation error if required fields missing             | Medium | Auto-wait, robust locators, assert visible errors            |
| TC-CHAOS-04 | Chaos      | Rapid refresh & submit                     | Start filling → Rapidly refresh → Submit                                     | Form handled safely; no crash                           | High   | Auto-waits; observable UI assertion                          |
